The paper deals with the multiway cut problem, which is a classic problem in theoretical computer science and optimization. The problem is related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also proposes a preprocessing algorithm and discusses kernelization, which are topics related to parameterized complexity and computational complexity theory, suggesting that it could belong to categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
